<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbbb5d56d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s2000c–9"><num value="2000c–9">§ 2000c–9.</num><heading> Classification and assignment</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this subchapter shall prohibit classification and assignment for reasons other than race, color, religion, sex or national origin.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbbb5d56e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/352/tIV/s410">Pub. L. 88–352, title IV, § 410</ref>, <date date="1964-07-02">July 2, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/249">78 Stat. 249</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/92/318/tIX/s906/a">Pub. L. 92–318, title IX, § 906(a)</ref>, <date date="1972-06-23">June 23, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/375">86 Stat. 375</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbbb5d56f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbbb5d570-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbbb5d571-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1972—<ref href="/us/pl/92/318">Pub. L. 92–318</ref> inserted “sex” after “religion,”.</p>
</note>
